The tenant of Bakal: The stoves are heating up, he signed a higher rent.
An imposing elderly man walked out the door of the RPG Byty company's customer center from the "coal baron" Zdenek Bakal, the largest private owner of apartments for rent in the Czech Republic.
He had under his arm a file with three new rental contracts for three apartments: his own, his daughter’s and his son’s who is serving a sentence.
Deregulation has increased the rent for these three people.
Instead of paying 3500 the son will have to pay from next year for a 2+1 apartment of second category 4100 crowns.
“And there is no hot water and the heating is running on solid fuel,” points to his son’s new contract as the man with the signing power.
"But I signed anyway," he said, angry and half resigned.
The citizen association of the BytyOKD.cz apartments, which described the new rental conditions as "immoral and indecent", advises tenants not to sign and wait until December 7, when a notice will be published to explain the method to be followed to claim.
But the man reacts to this with a gesture of the hand.
"One says that, the other says something else" while frowning.
The Ostrava region becomes the laboratory of deregulation.
After the New Year, this is what awaits most apartments in the Czech Republic whose rents do not match the market price.
Aktualne.cz has therefore decided to visit the "laboratory" personally.
The RPG waiting room in Havirovska Street is one of four in the Ostrava region and it is already full on Tuesdays at 9am.
Right next to the door stands a guard of a security company with a device to call customers.
A special button, "rent 2011", is turned on on the touch screen.
A single press and paper with a number comes out of the device.
You don't have time to read your "157" number as your number is already starting to light up on the big screen under the waiting room topit.
In a fraction of a second, it's your turn.
After a short while, an old couple arrives to inquire about the rent, but the new rents do not seem to concern people in the waiting room.
The majority of people have come to solve common problems like everywhere else - demands for repairs, insurance-related events and the like.
In the Ostrava region, people from more than 44,000 apartments in the RPG portfolio have been receiving mail with new leases in their mailbox since about mid-November.
RPG Byty offers them rent increases of 15 to 38 percent.
the special window for new rents has been open to the public since November 18.
"It's been working for almost a week, so it's still on trial," replies, after a moment of hesitation, the employee behind the counter when the customer presents himself as a journalist.
Deragulation and the old miners’ apartments of Bakal are a very sensitive local subject.
The vice-president of the parliament and native of the Ostrava region Lubomir Zaoralek of the social democrats reported fairly strongly before the elections and it now fills the local newspapers.
“Twenty years after them, I want a new floor.”
"They didn't even change me a put...n of board in the toilet, relieves himself in introduction the man mentioned.
However, it is mostly, according to employees, retirees who come to make sure they will receive a discount on the new rent price if they sign up now as promised RPG in a special offer.
This is a discount of half the amount of the rent that will be received by the other renters who have signed their new contract before December 15.
But the "deregulation" counter on Havirovaska street is really not overwhelmed by the questions.
“Of the 360 customers who came yesterday, only 40 to 50 came for the rent,” the employee said at the counter.
And yet RPG displays both on its website and in the windows of individual interviews on rents when necessary.
If both parties do not agree on the rent, an independent tribunal will make the decision.
"It's not about threats, it's only about informing people about the unique and legitimate way to act legally," RPG said on its website.
“Nobody’s going to court here,” one of RPG Byty’s employees thinks, and the man on the street in front of the customer center agrees.
“I have 13,000 crowns of retirement and I have 5,000 crowns left to eat, I don’t have enough to go to court,” he said.
The employee suddenly feels uncomfortable.
"We'll see."
"Mr. Zaoralek in the media asks that no one sign and therefore people wait," she said.
Rent regulation ends in the Czech Republic with the beginning of 2011 and increases, according to RPG Byty, are an economic necessity.
“And, moreover, current rents still do not reach the level necessary for the simple maintenance of the fund for housing,” recalls Pavel Klimes, director of the residential portfolio of the company RPG Byty, that it is precisely the negligence of the fund for housing that makes the tenant angry is the main reason for the increase in rent.
However in 5 years between 2005 and 2010 RPG could with rents invest in apartments 4 billion, in four years from 2011 to 2014 this should make 5.2 billion.
The large screen hanging on the ceiling in front of the upholstered armchairs of the waiting room on Havirosvka street, however, repeats some information indicated in red.
The rent increase in 2011 is 15 percent and concerns no less than 31,200 apartments or more than 90 percent of RPG apartments.
"And it will always be at most 7.50 Czech crowns per m2 per month," the screen says.
The 38 percent increase concerns only 400 apartments in the RPG portfolio.
"In these cases, this is a really low increase of 19.66 Czech kroner per m2," adds RPG.
Next year the rent will remain the same for 2,600 apartments.
RPG Byty promises that deregulation will not cause a radical but gradual increase over 4 to 8 years.
It adds other commitments: all the money from the increase in rents (cf. the graph) is returned to the apartments in the form of savings in heating - new windows and heating.
Those who sign the agreement on the rent increase have priority.
The kindergarten is also part of the offices that included the architects.
The administrative building Avriopoint in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected it to also house a mini kindergarten with everything you need - colorful walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October of last year, children of Arch. design employees can go there.
The architectural project company Arch. Design, whose workshops have produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has designed its mini nursery school since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, mostly of child-bearing age, and it was important for it that women architects and project managers could quickly return to work.
Along with reduced-time employment contracts, the nursery school is a bonus offered to its employees by the company Arch. Design. as part of its social program.
Builders and architects have the opportunity to combine work that takes care of children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who imagined this nursery school and with the support of the management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini-kindergarten is financed by the European Social Fund through the Operational Programme for Human Resources and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the funding (up to 2.8 million Czech crowns), they were able to buy equipment and appliances and after two years ensure a qualified staff as well as the start-up.
After the use of the funding endowment (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project lasted a year and it was the company Economy rating that helped to apply for the grant.
Care for children is provided by qualified staff, all day a nurse and a kindergarten teacher take care of the children. the children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they are more than three years oldfor the most part.
As this is a "mini kindergarten" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace themselves.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it involves individual care and education, the curriculum of the mini-kindergarten is comparable to that of pre-school education.
Children do not only play there, but quality teaching is also assured - from the beginning to the preparation for school benches we teach English.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of small children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and not have the stress of a delay to pick up the children in a school away from the parents' workplace.
Parents therefore use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty is created between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design. is thus one of the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens HR marketing.
The bone house still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look at Gaudi's interiors.
The roof looks like the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase looks like a dinosaur spine and the balconies look like open fish mouths.
This is how the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by architect Antoni Gaudi is.
Due to its organic forms, the house has received from the locals the nickname of Bone House.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaic, facade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present curves, this is all that is ypic for the Art Nouveau of Antoni Gaudi.
The front facade of the house unfolds its dream lines, its colors and pleasant textures that remind nature and animals.
During a more detailed observation we see the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought with precision.
In the night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of color brilliance is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
The wood copies in waves the window frames, the railings, the decorative elements of the doors, the eyelet and the slats.
The Battlo house, which stands in the Eixample district in the Passeig de Gracia shopping street at number 43, was born from the construction of an 1877 house by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, initially insisted on demolishing the old construction and building another brand new one but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-unit house was not conceived by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on his project that were born the decorations for an apartment representing the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade.
For the facade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work for the plans of Casa Battlo began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudi Casa Mila's house and Park Guell in which there are other works by Gaudi.
The locals nicknamed the hot house just after it was finished because of its organic shapes "the Bone House".
Others, having regard to the specific mechanism of opening the windows called it "the house that bleated".
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of St. George the patron of Catalonia.
Other sculptural elements of the construction contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi has designed for the house a unique system in its time of central heating, with ventilation vents and typical fireplaces.
Their 45-degree tilt looks odd.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not respect the construction guidelines of the time and did not let himself be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the building permit, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the finishing the city council was horrified and asked for modifications.
For example, it did not please the members of the municipal council that the pillars of the construction were encroaching on the public sidewalk.
There was never any change, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the city's call Josep Battlo requested (and obtained satisfaction) permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and on the third a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase that leads to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled out by the basic elements of the reconstruction and their replacement by curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of connecting spaces.
The common part can be connected completely by opening the doors of the salons and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit the private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with Gaudi's reconstruction received besides new facades a non-traditional roof and two floors more.
Gaudi's play with light is also impressive, with blue and white glazed tiles with which is decorated the inner courtyard and with the skylights.
The two-color play gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was enough simply to bet on the principle that the white reflects more than the dark which on the contrary absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house which was inscribed in 2005 in the Unesco World Heritage Fund can be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous designer.
They continued the visits as they found it to be a lucrative venture and they expanded the scope of visits to the common areas and attic including the roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, pensioners, groups and tourist card holders have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the price of entry into Gaudi's other buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you must quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and completely visit the house.
How to choose a mattress and a box spring: women have other criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the surface reserved for bed, so the mattress and bed base give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a concrete user.
During the choice several things are determining,: the weight, height, age, state of health as well as the gender of the owner.
The type of interior in which we will place the mattress and the box spring is also important.
A typical example?
For example in the country house where we do not sleep continuously latex mattresses are not appropriate because they "warm up" gently.
In addition, they weigh more than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they also do not have enough ventilation channels in the heart and if they remain, in addition, on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also form there.
Habit is also decisive in choice.
Those who spend time abroad, where very thick mattresses with a softening layer are frequently used, will hardly feel good on a low and hard surface.
“That’s how all the hokeyists who come back from NHL complain that they can’t sleep there.”
"For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a foaming layer of laziness."
"Such mattresses are also recommended for people who suffer from diabetes who have a nervous system disorder that therefore mis-assume "information" of the joints and skin," explains Sylva Adamczikova who specializes in upholstered furniture.
That's why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered the hokeyists as well as other customers.
“Today everything works well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico have for example appropriate mattresses.
You don’t have to be an NHL guy to be able to enjoy a lazy moss.
This “miracle” just works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape according to the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won’t turn around in the night like after a tough game.
You just sleep better.
Lazy foam also works as a protection against squaring.
To choose the mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, about 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman with a height of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220 cm.
The minimum width for each for a double bed should be 90 cm or in total 180 cm.
For single beds, singles for example, it is recommended to take at least 120 / 140 cm.
It is convenient in case of a visit.
"However it is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when you are lying on your back you should lay your hands comfortably with your elbows slightly bent. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Bodybuilders and Decorators who has been dedicated for several years to the problem of healthy sleep and ergonomics of furniture and teaches it in specialized schools.
For a bed with two places each needs its own box spring and mattress, so be careful however during the achât to choose the height of the mattress.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the bed base at different heights and this is not feasible on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, this count for the shape and ventilation layer at least three centimeters.
"When touching or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a specific type of bed base.
The bed-sleeper, when the mattress and bed base are united like Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
Mattresses abate very badly; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night one normally sweats from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to recall a large (and clogged) sieve.
For this, specialists refuse to advertise for a 25-year lifetime for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But everything to his but.
And for this an experience advice from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, give up, for the coating of the mattress, hygiene or washing but rather add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to manufacture coatings with zipper for the whole, that is to say that after the opening we have two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine it is very important!) otherwise the handling for large models (and for one person) becomes when they are removed a fight between a light weight and a heavy weight on a ring.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a box spring?
Ever!
Maximum for a bed intended for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are none) with air holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with sachet springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and a layer of air.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of a bed of this type.
For single-position slatted beds with 14/18 slats, latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (perhaps the combination of latex and coconut), are ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are doubled in the lower part of the kidneys and it is thus possible to regulate the rigidity.
For multi-position mattresses, you should not take a spring mattress because it does not respond to changes in position.
In addition to adjusting the stiffness of the slats, you can also install what is called a shoulder cradle.
It is a special connection of the slats that makes it possible to press or even tilt the slat so that the shoulder of the sleeper "integrates" well.
For men who have "shoulders as wide as their backs," that's really an important thing.
This thing is already being considered by mattress manufacturers who for the "masculine" have started to use a softening area at the shoulders.
But they also think of women - they again offer them a softer surface at the hips.
For the most difficult customer there are wing or pad bases with what is called a multi-force suspension.
The pressure spreads in more points and diinuates the tension.
But of course, be careful, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and inflated with air) on good mattresses and box springs, the "plus" disappears.
The basic rule is a simple pillow: the pillow must support the head and its tips must reach only the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm that Scandinavians by example prefer.
When lying on the side, the pillow should level (with the shoulder cradle of the bed base or the area slammed into the mattress) the height of the shoulders.
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the first ones based on straw and herbs.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also towards organic mattresses.
Petrol-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is made, are replaced by natural oils, such as soybean oil.
Almost all known manufacturers use soy.
“The organic label for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products,” says Petr vasicek of Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used for mattress coatings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop forest or lavender scents.
There are differences between man and woman.
While birch plant extract for the mattress coating absorbs heat and cools the body, "cools" the man, the coatings "heat" the women.
Red pepper extract speeds up blood circulation and is therefore warmer for the weak sex.
The current favorites?
Mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disturbed cell structure so more breathable than standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different rigidities of cold foams gives polyzone mattresses that know exactly where the head, lower back and feet are.
You will pay a quality mattress from 7000 kroner and more.
Those who are characterized by their health parameters have less VAT and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex reached first place.
Saving for the mattress and the box spring is not easy.
One may from time to time have in connection with special actions on the part of the manufacturers or producers two mattresses for the price of only one.
For example, Magniflex offers Duofreeze mattresses with memory foam sewn to the coating for 11990 crowns.
Of course, you can take the second one for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cell structure and a great thickness was started with Tempur material at a "cosmic" pace.
This started as matter for NASA because astronauts were undergoing huge load factors at startup.
The Tempur softens in heat and hardens, on the contrary, in cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes optimal pressure.
It is therefore ideal for sleeping poorly and for an increase in comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special cushions for the feet that relieve the legs and the venous system.
For example, Czech manufacturers use EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or the same type.
Devices to track people are increasingly in demand by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear for their child leads more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars can just as well be used to trace the movement of people and help in some cases such as for example that of the little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as big as a matchbox but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka moved a large number of people and they began to look for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
“We are trying to tell everyone that this is not espionage but only another way to reduce the likelihood of another tragedy,” said Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, one of the suppliers of tracking devices in the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases."
“The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for security reasons,” Pilin adds.
According to him children should always know for what purpose is used "the box" and how to use it in case of emergency.
Child psychologist Dana Bockova draws attention to the fact that if the child does not want to carry such a thing, he will get rid of it.
“And even the little ones can show great creativity when it comes to purposely getting rid of something when they don’t want to be under control.”
“Mobile phones, which can cut off like these tracking devices, have already brought parents to long waits,” Bockova says.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in case of aggression is very questionable.
"If it is a prepared abduction, the author will do everything so that the child does not have an electronic device that can locate him."
“Currently, it’s the phone.”
"As soon as the tracking devices develop, they (criminals) will also look for them because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign."
“In such cases the criminals will always be ahead of the police,” says the psychologist.
She admits that such devices can help in an unprepared attack by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the case of an assault.
"The device can be configured in such a way that it is in regular emission after a specified period of time."
“In the event that the device is destroyed, it still remains the last position of the person concerned.”
“The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who slipped and ends up in a lying position without moving,” Cech said.
According to him, so-called smart mobile phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with a special software package.
The problem with current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those worn as a matchbox-sized pendant or to smaller telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of the Macro Weil company, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that look like common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the possible attacker will not be able to recognize the tracing device."
"Or he will realize it after a while, which will have given the police a little more time," he added.
Whether the tracing device is developed in the form of a bracelet or pendant, it will always use the same technology as for tracing cars.
It is a combination of position acquisition systems using GPS (which is commonly used in autonavigation) and a mobile phone function that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
