No one expected to have a perfect general election in Haiti on November 28.
But it was far worse than the outsiders who wanted to help the disaster-stricken and fear-stricken country.
Polling boxes and a new ballot were presented, ballots scattered in the goutières, polling stations ransacked and intimidation
The polling stations opened late at night.
Many Haitians, including many who were displaced by the January earthquake, were wandering around to find where to vote.
