A dozen presidential candidates, including several suspected favourites, denounced the fraud and called for the cancellation of the election.
Protests, sometimes violent, have exploded across the country.
Nevertheless, Edmond Mulet, the senior official in Haiti of the United Nations, considers the event as "a fairly good election in many ways".
Observers for the Organization of American States and the Caribbean Community have cautiously stated that they "do not believe that these irregularities, however serious, necessarily invalidated the process."
In other words, the show continues.
