The other two show dogs out of four stolen from outside a motel in Bellflower have been found, Los Angeles County Sheriffs announced Thursday.
The four show dogs - two akitas and two Welsh pembroke corgis - disappeared Tuesday when someone stole the Chevrolet Express pickup truck in which they had spent the night outside a Bellflower motel 6, authorities said.
Two of the dogs were recovered Wednesday afternoon and the other two were found late Wednesday evening, Los Angeles County Sheriff’s Department spokesman Steve Whitmore told AFP.
“The good news is that dogs are fine,” Whitmore says.
"They are in good shape."
“They were returned to their rightful owners.”
Whitmore refused to say exactly where the dogs had been found, in what neighborhood and under what circumstances they were found.
"An investigation is ongoing."
“We don’t want to say it,” Whitmore said.
“We are following orders.”
The owners of the dogs, Kristina Rickard and David Peek, could not be reached to provide a comment Thursday.
They were reunited Wednesday afternoon with their two Akitas at a county animal shelter in Downey.
Sheriff's deputies found the van and the two dogs separately in Compton.
The Akitas - Trace, a 3-year-old male, and Didi, a 10-month-old female - were safe, authorities said.
