“Pakistan has had to hire personnel with strict religious beliefs to protect nuclear facilities; given the decline in educational and cultural levels, extremist organizations have more opportunities to recruit people who work in nuclear or missile programs,” said Yuri Korolev, an expert at Russia’s Ministry of External Affairs, during a meeting with his U.S. counterparts.
The new documentation filtered through Julian Assange’s portal is the increasingly reduced cooperation between the United States and Pakistan in the field of nuclear proliferation and Pakistan’s high degree of nuclear armament production.
